race.comment: VORTISTAR (6) is a leader who deserved his Maiden win over 1400m at the track. This doesn't look any harder and he's back after 7 days so he must be pleasing. He can go on with it now. CALLED THROUGH (7) comes out of the same race and was cruelled by the 13 gate. He finished hard beaten a nose prior and will be looking to sit handier this time. Has a chance if that occurs. WYNDINTHEWILLOWS (13) switched from a Victorian yard and needed the outing. He's won a Hobart trial since and the longer distance suits. She has ability so keep onside. THICKSKINNED (5) finished on from back in the field here last time after a big Maiden win on the synthetic. He should be around the mark.
